        <td bgcolor="dimgray" colspan="2" valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="1">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/15/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 08:10:42</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=2338"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=2338')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=2780&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Possible+bug+with+p%2Fd+counters+and+resists"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> <BR>Chilling embrace was recently changed to add poison counters. When this change was made, the spell started to become heavily resisted while it had previously been easy to land on most mobs. </P><P>I see three scenarios here:</P><P>- Chilling embrace was too hard to resist before the change, and was tweaked with a worse resist roll (unlikely). </P><P>- Poison and disease counters make spells easier to resist on purpose (possible, but if so I think we should have been given an explanation). </P><P>- Poison and disease counters are bugged, making spells easier to resist. </P><P><BR>I believe that poison / disease counters are bugged, possibly similar to the ancient bug with druid DD roots. Perhaps do p/d counters give the spell an additional resist roll, making it harder to land.</P><P>It is also very likely that spells with p/d counters generate an extra amount of agro. This would be consistent with the agro associated with for example cessation of cor, and with shaman observations since slows started to add disease counters. </P><P>If this is indeed a bug, it has a huge impact on our spell lines (scent of terris, ebolt, cessation of cor). With lower resist rates and possibly lower agro, these spells would be much more useful to necros.</P><P>Maybe something for Jahaar to look into?</P><P><BR>Zarloth V`Sharatouum<BR>Teir`dal Warlock<BR>Vallon Zek<BR></font></td>

